<subSubSection id="9CAD66EAED7955C2E6211F3A3F6F4267" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="70C842899486B36B7D1D241FAC2F19E1" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="23DFD5AF2C8CA0E1D038D18E6DB2D101" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">A var, typo floribus grandioribus, sepalis 11 - 12 mm longis, corolla 2.5-3 cm longa, plerumque alba, in centro atropurpurea.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C4EE3C0522FAFAA56CB8EF8570981599" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<taxonomicName id="88054EFDF0BA406E05C7F352DADF7BB5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sagittifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittifolius">
<emphasis id="B0221C9ABFE2D978D0FBE3FBD58A817E" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Convolvulus sagittifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="EE39AFDBE1C1C4B3CBC1ADEBCF077DEF" author="Scheele, A" journalOrPublisher="Linnaea" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="747 - 755" refId="B319" refString="Scheele, A, 1849. Beitraege zur Flor von Texas: Convolvulaceae. Linnaea 21: 747 - 755" title="Beitraege zur Flor von Texas: Convolvulaceae." volume="21" year="1849">Scheele (1849</bibRefCitation>
: 747), nom illeg., non 
<taxonomicName id="EEBEECC27970F1B36CE303292CC0A740" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sagittifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittifolius">
<emphasis id="DA01BFF55E3223170563645FD577FFAC" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Convolvulus sagittifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Michx. (1803).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F7A7114DD7C4B276416669C16E3BD20" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="62F621763E011F5AC3C8421DCDC82F34" bold="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Type.</emphasis>
Texas, 
<normalizedToken id="8C55DC6D92055223DDDD56701C63095B" originalValue="“Neubraunfels”">&quot;Neubraunfels&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis id="B7563C22F6F36E86885B3B47FFFAF1CA" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Lindheimer</emphasis>
s.n. (B†).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FE6C200F3182320EB333D9FD3910394" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="type">
<paragraph id="86FDA7E88F6AC74557F5128BE20AAA21" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D64863BECD09BEC0A6C87E09F05C7F8" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, Texas, New Braunfels, 
<emphasis id="980C6262348900A7AE31BD6C551B061B" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">F. Lindheim</emphasis>
er, fasc. IV No. 469 (holotype K; isotypes BM, FHO, LE, P, W).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0916412E529D5AF46A3BEF29EE2697AB" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="CD5748730FD2B59632955CFB46B0BBA9" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5BC4F55B62E1416D72CE642A5E56E610" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Distinguished by it is larger flowers; sepals 11-12 mm long; corolla 2.5-3 cm long, usually white but often with a dark centre.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4081543F46F6BACD24057A04514DA6BB" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E187361663B6774629907A42A96EF9D7" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="370816B7594E895B5F9CA7353F5CAADD" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
United States, Texas: widely distributed but not common in at least seven Texan counties (
<emphasis id="0609C68B9154F8AB1F50CCC096B9D841" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Lindheimer</emphasis>
fasc. 3: 469, 
<emphasis id="C7E8F15F0B7386701C5032B35A7C7367" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Siedo</emphasis>
447, 
<emphasis id="4DB94B7DBB23D76767A16E0E60D4CD7A" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Logan Smith</emphasis>
774, 
<emphasis id="5AB2853FB20125881457AC276834DF41" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Hutchins</emphasis>
1035).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E51024B3806BCD147284C5DD9170FF08" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="notes">
<paragraph id="69310C14EC7D21E71554443B7505253A" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BED0C3215DA8FB1CE156833B93F8B54A" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
Intermediates with 
<taxonomicName id="2C8F90A821594C6130464A8FCEE4FDF5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. var. var. equitans" order="Solanales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="sagittifolius" subSpecies="var." variety="equitans">var. equitans</taxonomicName>
occur and 
<taxonomicName id="0AC3BF03708875EF4B63EFEEDD4FE24A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. var. var. lindheimeri" order="Solanales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="sagittifolius" subSpecies="var." variety="lindheimeri">var. lindheimeri</taxonomicName>
may have arisen as a result of hybridisation between 
<taxonomicName id="D58FF7AF53119791DC9DF8AAE1C5A7C8" authorityName="B. L. Turner, Phytologia 91: 394. 2009. (Turner" authorityYear="2009" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus carrii" order="Solanales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carrii">
<emphasis id="208C7A2A37353BB565107D4F2B24EAF5" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Convolvulus carrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7B695F88A113492F69463E3EB9609454" authorityName="Benth., Pl. Hartw. 16. 1839. (Bentham" authorityYear="1839" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus equitans" order="Solanales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="equitans">
<emphasis id="BFB112F1E1A0230DD9F5E4D29425C874" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Convolvulus equitans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
although it is not sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="FBEF33129E6A9FCF8F6348AC50E38FBC" authorityName="B. L. Turner, Phytologia 91: 394. 2009. (Turner" authorityYear="2009" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus carrii" order="Solanales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carrii">
<emphasis id="27C7592B6B99296D93188771FF1DBABF" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Convolvulus carrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
